## Architecture

```
src/
├── main.py          Entry point — FastAPI app, routers, lifespan
├── config.py        All settings via pydantic-settings (reads .env)
├── models.py        Request/response Pydantic schemas
{% if profile in ["rag", "full"] %}
├── components/      Low-level retrieval primitives
│   ├── hybrid_retriever.py   Combines dense + sparse search
│   └── reranker.py           Cross-encoder reranking
├── services/        Orchestration layer
│   ├── rag_pipeline.py       End-to-end query → answer
│   ├── semantic_cache.py     Embedding-based result cache
│   ├── conversation.py       Multi-turn memory management
│   ├── query_rewriter.py     LLM-powered query expansion
│   └── query_router.py       Route queries to right pipeline
├── prompts/         Versioned prompt management
└── security/        Three-layer guard: input → content → output
{% endif %}
{% if profile in ["agent", "full"] %}
├── agents/          Agentic layer with self-correction
│   ├── document_grader.py    Grade retrieved docs for relevance
│   ├── query_decomposer.py   Break complex queries into sub-queries
│   ├── adaptive_router.py    LLM-driven pipeline selection
│   └── tools/               Pluggable tool definitions
{% endif %}
```

## Key Conventions

- All settings come from `src/config.py` → `settings` singleton. Never hardcode API keys.
- Models use Pydantic v2. Prefer `model_validate` over `parse_obj`.
- Async-first: all I/O-bound functions should be `async def`.
- Tests live in `tests/` and use pytest. Run with `uv run pytest`.

## Running Locally

```bash
cp .env.example .env   # fill in API keys
uv sync
uv run uvicorn src.main:app --reload
```
